[2] Cholera - Sierra Leone
Date: Wed 22 Aug 2012
Source: WHO Global Alert and Response (GAR), Disease Outbreak News [edited]
http://www.who.int/csr/don/2012_08_22/en/index.html


Since the beginning of 2012, Sierra Leone has recorded 11 653 cases of cholera, with 216 deaths (case fatality rate of 1.9 percent). The rate of new cases has accelerated rapidly since the beginning of August 2012: since then, 5706 cases have been recorded, and 2 new districts, Bonthe and Kono, have been affected by the epidemic. 10 of the country's 13 districts are now registering cases and this spread emphasizes the need to rapidly scale up the response. The 2 most heavily affected districts are Western Area and Tonkolili.

WHO is supporting Sierra Leone in the areas of epidemiology, social mobilization and surveillance. WHO has deployed 2 epidemiologists, and 3 cholera experts from Zimbabwe to support coordination, public information, social mobilization, case management and infection control.

WHO does not recommend that any travel or trade restrictions be applied to Sierra Leone.

