[3] Cholera - Guinea
Date: Thu 23 Aug 2012
Source: Agence France-Presse (AFP) [edited]
http://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5i-8I9vkXKD3NzA6lH5JbsgVJhaFA?docId=CNG.185ed25d673613589cc359cfe5cb2bd9.2c1


An outbreak of cholera in Guinea has killed 60 people since February 2012 and is showing no signs of letting up, the country's health ministry said Thu 23 Aug 2012.

Officials have registered 2054 cases, with the capital Conakry and the southwestern city of Forecariah worst affected. 13 people have died in Conakry and 23 in Forecariah.

Sierra Leone, Mali, and Niger have also been hard hit, with high levels of malnourishment as a result of a drought exacerbating the problem.

